From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: RAX3000Q <dev@rax3000q>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath11k: fix memory segment count for unknown QMI types

Increment idx in the default switch case for unknown QMI memory types
(e.g., type 10 from dual-QCN6122 firmware 2.7.0.1-01744). This
maintains idx == i alignment, so the subsequent mem_seg_count = idx
correctly reflects the original firmware request count.

Without this fix, skipping the idx increment causes later known-type
entries to write to target_mem[idx] at the compressed position,
overwriting the unknown type's entry. The resulting segment count and
order mismatch causes the Q6 firmware to ASSERT in err_smem_ver.2.1.

Signed-off-by: RAX3000Q <dev@rax3000q>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/qmi.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/qmi.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/qmi.c
@@ -2112,7 +2112,8 @@ static int ath11k_qmi_assign_target_mem_chunk(struct ath11k_base *ab)
 		default:
 			ath11k_warn(ab, "qmi ignore invalid mem req type %d\n",
 				    ab->qmi.target_mem[i].type);
-			break;
+			idx++;
+			break;
 		}
 	}
 	ab->qmi.mem_seg_count = idx;
